                    Enforcement & Legal Services Division

       The Enforcement & Legal Services Division (ELS) is one of three
    operational divisions under the California Corporations Commissioner.
      ELS is headed by an Assistant Commissioner and is responsible for
    enforcing the laws under the Investment and Lender-Fiduciary Programs
               administered by the Department of Corporations.


